Numeric value types
- interger
- number
- dimension 
- percentage

Lengths
- absolute 
- relative 

Absolute
- alway the same
- px

Relative
- can change based on context
- em and rem for font size
- prefer rem

1em 
- for font size of el. parent
- Ex: el. font site 16px then 4em is 16 x 4

1rem
- font size of the root element (:root or html)
- math same as em but no need to track parent element 
- recomended

Viewport unists
1vh - equal to 1% of the viewport height
1vw - equal to 1% of the viewport width


Percentages
- relative to some other value. For example, if you set an element's font-size as a percentage, 
 it will be a percentage of the font-size of the element's parent.
 If you use a percentage for a width value, it will be a percentage of the width of the parent.

Color
- keywords
- hexadecimal 
	#ffc0cb read grean blue PAR FORM rgb color
- rbg()
	rgb(2 121 139)
	rgb(2 121 139 / .3)
		- last param alpha 0 fully transparete 1 fully opaqe (values betwwen gives different levels of transparency)
- hue
	- value tell difference or similarity betwwen colors 
	- can be specify as <angle> because it uses color wheel https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Glossary/Color_wheel
	- can be sprifcy using function hwb or hsl
		- hwb base, whitnesses, blackneses, optional alptha transparency
		- hsl base, sasturation, lightness, optional alptha transparency 
			hsl(188 97% 28%)
			hsl(188 97% 28% / .3
			
Image
- image pointed by url function
- image file
- gradient			
- example
`	we are using an image and a gradient as values for the CSS background-image property
	.gradient {
		background-image: linear-gradient(
			90deg,
			rgb(119 0 255 / 39%),
			rgb(0 212 255 / 25%)
  );

background-position: right 60px;
	- horizontally then vertical value defailt center 

Functions
- calc(), which lets you do operations like addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division.
- suport for math function to perform calculation
- calc(), which lets you do operations like addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division.
	-  width: calc(20% + 100px);
- list https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Values_and_Units/CSS_Value_Functions 	

